 ('106', '93', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Muay Thai\",\"slug\":\"muay-thai\",\"postDate\":1465961400,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"6\",\"fields\":{\"5\":{\"94\":{\"type\":\"secondaryHero\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Muay Thai\",\"body\":\"<p><strong>Muay Thai: Adults<\\/strong><br><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Muay Thai is a combat sport from Thailand that uses stand-up strikes along with various clinch techniques. This physical and mental discipline is known as \\\"the art of eight limbs\\\" because it is characterized by the combined use of fists, elbows, knees and shins during training.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"contactButton\":\"1\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#000000\",\"backgroundImage\":[\"40\"],\"mapTitle\":\"\",\"mapContent\":\"\",\"mapAddress\":\"\",\"flexibleArea\":\"\"}},\"95\":{\"type\":\"oneColumn\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"\",\"body\":\"<p>Individuals participating in this program achieve outstanding physical conditioning due to the highly intense yet fun&nbsp;nature of striking through the use of bag&nbsp;drills, mitt drills&nbsp;and pad work. This self paced class is taught by high level instructors with years of training in this discipline, who encourage each participant to reach their full physical potential. &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#ffffff\",\"backgroundImage\":[\"12\"]}}},\"22\":\"Muay Thai: Adults\",\"4\":\"\",\"3\":\"\"}}', '2016-06-27 01:43:36', '2016-06-27 01:43:36', 'f19108a3-e919-45ba-a670-608aee76b0c5'),
 ('107', '96', '3', '1', 'en_us', '3', '', '{\"typeId\":\"4\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Leadership\",\"slug\":\"leadership\",\"postDate\":1465961460,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"6\",\"fields\":{\"5\":{\"97\":{\"type\":\"secondaryHero\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Leadership\",\"body\":\"<p>The FPMA Leadership Program is an instructor recommended program. Students must first attain a blue belt through the Intermediate Program. They must also demonstrate leadership qualities to receive nominations.<\\/p>\",\"contactButton\":\"1\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#000000\",\"backgroundImage\":[\"8\"],\"mapTitle\":\"\",\"mapContent\":\"\",\"mapAddress\":\"\",\"flexibleArea\":\"\"}},\"98\":{\"type\":\"oneColumn\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"\",\"body\":\"<p>The FPMA Leadership Program focuses on developing leaders, not only in Martial Arts, but in the community as well. Each month leadership students are required to demonstrate and apply a new leadership skill at home, at school, and in the Martial&nbsp;Arts training.<\\/p>\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#ffffff\",\"backgroundImage\":[\"12\"]}}},\"22\":\"\",\"4\":\"\",\"3\":\"\"}}', '2016-06-27 01:43:49', '2016-06-27 01:43:49', '89b3903d-af2c-43fe-9a6a-241a79bc89d0'),
 ('108', '73', '3', '1', 'en_us', '5', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"About Freddie\",\"slug\":\"about-freddie\",\"postDate\":1465959360,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"5\",\"fields\":{\"5\":{\"75\":{\"type\":\"secondaryHero\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"About Freddie\",\"body\":\"<p>Freddie Poole began martial arts training in 1981, at the age of seven years old. He began studying at Southwest Karate Academy under Demetrius \\u201cGolden Greek\\u201d Havanas. Southwest Karate Academy produced some of the best martial arts champions and competitors in the world, at that time. The 80\\u2019s were the tail end of the \\u201cTexas Blood and Guts\\u201d era of martial arts. The lineage began with Jhoon Rhee and his first black belt was Allen Steen. Steen went on to train many black belts and students and Texas was known for producing some of the best fighters in the country. Tim Kirby, Billye Jackson, Raymond McCallum, Santae Wilson Jr. and Cliff Thomas were some of the world-class competitors who had influence over Poole\\u2019s training and development.<\\/p>\",\"contactButton\":\"1\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#000000\",\"backgroundImage\":[\"36\"],\"mapTitle\":\"\",\"mapContent\":\"\",\"mapAddress\":\"\",\"flexibleArea\":\"\"}},\"76\":{\"type\":\"oneColumn\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"\",\"body\":\"<h3>As a young brown belt, Poole began teaching at Sun Belt Karate Academy by assisting younger and lower ranking students with warm-ups, kick punch technique and forms. It was not uncommon to see Poole leading an adult class at 12 years old.<\\/h3>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Poole received his 1st degree black belt in 1986, under Tim Kirby, Billye Jackson and Raymond McCallum. Poole competed in the AOK and was a top ranked competitor in forms and fighting for many years as a junior competitor.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Poole began training with long time friend and kickboxing champion Guy Mezger in 1993. Poole began honing his boxing and kickboxing skills with Mezger, Billye Jackson, Santae Wilson Jr. and Coach Charles Brown and went on to win a national title in 1997, which earned a spot on the US National Kickboxing team.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Poole\\u2019s boxing experience comes from training with some of the best coaches in the business. Phil Sawyer and Olympic Boxing Bronze medalist Charles Brown have influenced Poole in his boxing training, as well as Golden Gloves Champion Alex Andrade.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Poole has several years of Muay Thai experience, training with Francisco Sanchez of New World Combat, as well as World Muay Thai champion and MMA veteran Pete Spratt and Muay Thai champion Jason House.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Poole\\u2019s Judo experience comes from training with Master Vince Tamura and Judo Black Belt Rico Castro.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Poole currently trains under the tutelage of 8th degree Brazilian Jiu Jitsu master, Carlos Machado, where he holds a brown belt and is a proud affiliate of Machado Jiu Jitsu. Poole has also trained with many talented Brazilian Jiu Jitsu black belts including Kenny McClure, Jeff Sawyer, Rico Castro and Taryn Douglas.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Poole has competed all over the United States and internationally in Europe, winning a KICK International title in 2004 along with many team karate titles from 1999-2004. Poole also fought for Team Texas in Chuck Norris\\u2019s televised fight league, The World Combat League.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Poole has taken his vast knowledge of martial arts and created a well-rounded training system for all ages. Freddie Poole\\u2019s Martial Arts is the most balanced martial arts training system, combining traditional training elements with practical real world application. By integrating both of these elements into one system, one can truly train in mixed martial arts.<\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Since opening its doors in 2004, Freddie Poole\'s Martial Arts has been impacting thousands&nbsp;of&nbsp;lives in the community. Our friendly staff looks forward each day to helping our students achieve their goals. Although standards are set high, each student at FPMA is evaluated on an individual basis to ensure progression on their own timeline. This approach ensures students achieve and&nbsp;earn rank on their own merit.&nbsp;We encourage our students to trust the process and enjoy it. Earning a black belt at FPMA is a once in a lifetime experience!<\\/p>\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#000000\",\"backgroundImage\":[\"12\"]}}},\"4\":\"\",\"3\":\"\"}}', '2016-06-27 01:44:18', '2016-06-27 01:44:18', '58565750-5fa9-4fa7-874a-5a21258f5306'),
 ('109', '32', '3', '1', 'en_us', '5', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Contact Us\",\"slug\":\"contact-us\",\"postDate\":1458879660,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"5\":{\"59\":{\"type\":\"secondaryHero\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Contact Us\",\"body\":\"<p>Come see for yourself why our martial arts system has been so popular for so many years. Our black belt instructors are here to help you achieve all your marital art and fitness goals.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"contactButton\":\"\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#000000\",\"backgroundImage\":[\"37\"],\"mapTitle\":\"\",\"mapContent\":\"\",\"mapAddress\":\"\",\"flexibleArea\":\"\"}},\"60\":{\"type\":\"contact\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Contact Us\",\"body\":\"\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#f5f5f5\"}}},\"4\":\"\",\"3\":\"\"}}', '2016-06-27 01:46:22', '2016-06-27 01:46:22', '63a899a2-c03b-4d6f-bc60-59d72722b3c8'),
 ('110', '33', '3', '1', 'en_us', '8', '', '{\"typeId\":\"3\",\"authorId\":\"1\",\"title\":\"Specials\",\"slug\":\"specials\",\"postDate\":1458879720,\"expiryDate\":null,\"enabled\":1,\"parentId\":\"\",\"fields\":{\"5\":{\"55\":{\"type\":\"secondaryHero\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Specials\",\"body\":\"<p>We pride ourselves in offering superior service and training for parents and kids. Outside of our extensive martial arts programs offered at both of our Dallas locations, FPMA offers various extra personal services that are very educational, affordable and definitely FUN! From private birthday celebrations to women\\u2019s self-defense classes, there\\u2019s a special FPMA Extra for everyone.<\\/p>\",\"contactButton\":\"1\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#000000\",\"backgroundImage\":[\"40\"],\"mapTitle\":\"\",\"mapContent\":\"\",\"mapAddress\":\"\",\"flexibleArea\":\"\"}},\"56\":{\"type\":\"oneColumn\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Parent\\u2019s Nights Out\",\"body\":\"<p>Got a date night or hang out with the crew night planned and need somewhere to take the kiddos? Bring \\u2018em to FPMA for Parents Night Out (PNO). The PNO program is on specified Saturdays from 5-9pm and welcomes both FPMA students and non-members to join in on a night full of pizza, movies, prizes and fun. <strong><em>Oh, did we mention Nerf gun wars, too?<\\/em><\\/strong> <a href=\\\"\\/locations#entry:7:url\\\">Just give one of our locations a call<\\/a> for more information, pricing and dates for the next PNO.&nbsp;<\\/p>\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#ffffff\",\"backgroundImage\":[\"12\"]}},\"57\":{\"type\":\"oneColumn\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Birthday Parties\",\"body\":\"<p>Celebrate the birthday for your little martial artists Freddie Poole style! FPMA offers a personal experience with one of our many skilled instructors, ready to teach all of the little partiers some exciting new martial arts moves and put a unique spin on a birthday celebrations. Decorations, music and food are welcome. Interested in having your kid\\u2019s next birthday celebration at FPMA? <a href=\\\"tel:2143525425\\\">Give one of our locations a call<\\/a> for more information.<\\/p>\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#f5f5f5\",\"backgroundImage\":\"\"}},\"58\":{\"type\":\"oneColumn\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Special Events\",\"body\":\"<p><strong>FPMA is proud to announce our summer 2016 Karate Camp for kids.<\\/strong><\\/p>\\r\\n\\r\\n<p>Karate Camp is designed for children ages 4-11 and provides the perfect summer getaway for kids interested in learning more about the many forms of martial art. Give you kids the opportunity to learn more about boosting leadership and teamwork skills, building and improving self confidence, self defense techniques, bully awareness as well as fun martial arts games and drills. Choose from 2 summer camp sessions only a $25 deposit required to reserve a spot. Reach out to a FPMA location for more details.<\\/p>\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#ffffff\",\"backgroundImage\":\"\"}},\"77\":{\"type\":\"oneColumn\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Women\\u2019s Self Defense Seminars\",\"body\":\"<p>Safety for our members is a major priority for us. FPMA offers self-defense classes for women to learn how to protect themselves and their loved ones from unexpected attacks. Join FPMA for one of our Women\\u2019s Self Defense Seminars in partnership with Not Dead Yet Apparel. Come get hands-on training as we demonstrate various self-defense techniques, learn empowering safety awareness and practices. Attendance is always free, but we accept donations of $25 or more to benefit a designated local non-profit organization. Take the first step by contacting one of our locations for more information.<\\/p>\",\"backgroundColor\":\"#f5f5f5\",\"backgroundImage\":\"\"}},\"78\":{\"type\":\"oneColumn\",\"enabled\":\"1\",\"fields\":{\"heading\":\"Personal Training \",\"body\":\"<p>For the member who wants to learn 