ajor priority for us fpma offers self defense classes for women to learn how to protect themselves and their loved ones from unexpected attacks join fpma for one of our women s self defense seminars in partnership with not dead yet apparel come get hands on training as we demonstrate various self defense techniques learn empowering safety awareness and practices attendance is always free but we accept donations of $25 or more to benefit a designated local non profit organization take the first step by contacting one of our locations for more information women s self defense seminars ffffff for the member who wants to learn the valuable techniques of martial arts outside of a group setting fpma offers specialized one on one training sessions members get individually structured personal instruction from one of our certified martial arts trainers training sessions are customized to benefit each student in any skill level from a novice student wanting a more personal experience or an advanced student preparing for competition contact one of our two dallas locations for more details personal training '),
